description: Known as Vipās in Sanskrit sources, the modern Beas river, as well as the combined Beas-Sutlej, traverses parts of modern India and Pakistan. It was also known -- to varying degrees of clarity -- to Greek and Roman writers by the name variants Hypasis, Hyphasis, Bibasis, and Hypanis.
details: The Barrington Atlas Directory notes: Beas, as well as combined Beas-Sutlej stream IND/PAK Skt.: Vipās
